'''Clement Williams Kennedy Mundle''' (10 August 1916 – 27 July 1989) was a Scottish [[philosopher]]<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=The Continuum Encyclopedia of British Philosophy |title=Clement Williams Kennedy Mundle |url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803100216487}}</ref> and [[parapsychologist]].<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=Gale Encyclopedia of Occultism & Parapsychology |title=Clement Williams Kennedy Mundle |url=http://www.answers.com/topic/clement-williams-kennedy-mundle}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.survivalafterdeath.info/researchers/mundle.htm|title=C. W. K. Mundle|publisher=SurvivalAfterDeath.org.uk|accessdate=14 December 2013 |quote=Source (with minor modifications): The Society for Psychical Research, 1882-1982: A History by Renée Haynes (1982, Macdonald & Co (Publishers) Ltd, London).}}</ref> For many years he was Professor of philosophy at [[University College of North Wales, Bangor]].
