{{orphan|date=May 2017}}
[[File:Bressani - Discorsi sopra le obbiezioni fatte dal Galileo alla dottrina di Aristotile, 1760 - 1231591.jpg|thumb|''Discorsi sopra le obbiezioni fatte dal Galileo alla dottrina di Aristotile'', 1760]]
'''Gregorio Bressani''' (3 February 1703 &ndash; 12 January 1771) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[philosopher]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://thesaurus.cerl.org/cgi-bin/record.pl?rid=cnp02143629|title= Bressani, Gregorio (1703-1771) in CERL Thesaurus}}</ref>
Bressani was born in [[Treviso]]. He graduated from the [[University of Padua]] studying [[literature]] and [[philosophy]]. He was a dear friend of [[Francesco Algarotti]] although they had very different opinions. Bressani opposed [[Galileo Galilei|Galilei]] and [[Isaac Newton|Newton]] theories in favor of a more [[Scholasticism|scholastic]] approach.<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/gregorio-bressani_(Dizionario-Biografico)/|title= Bressani, Gregorio|work=Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani|publisher=Treccani|volume=14|year=1972}}</ref>
